#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs0.6"
msgid "9. Dutiyaupakkhaṭasikkhāpada"
msgstr "9. The second training rule on what is set aside"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.218"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.9.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.58"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2041"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa "
"ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena aññataro puriso aññataraṃ purisaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "At that time a certain man said to another man,"

#. VAR: ayyaṃ → ahaṃ ayyaṃ (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.3"
msgid "“ayyaṃ upanandaṃ cīvarena acchādessāmī”ti."
msgstr "“I“ll give a robe to Venerable Upananda.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.4"
msgid "Sopi evamāha—"
msgstr "And he replied,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.5"
msgid "“ahampi ayyaṃ upanandaṃ cīvarena acchādessāmī”ti."
msgstr "“I, too, will give a robe to Venerable Upananda.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.6"
msgid ""
"Assosi kho aññataro piṇḍacāriko bhikkhu tesaṃ purisānaṃ imaṃ kathāsallāpaṃ."
msgstr "A monk who was an alms-collector heard that conversation."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.7"
msgid "Atha kho so bhikkhu yenāyasmā upanando sakyaputto tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "He then went to Upananda"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.8"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ upanandaṃ sakyaputtaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.9"
msgid "“mahāpuññosi tvaṃ, āvuso upananda."
msgstr "“Upananda, you have much merit."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.10"
msgid "Amukasmiṃ okāse aññataro puriso aññataraṃ purisaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "I’ve just heard two men telling each other"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.11"
msgid "‘ayyaṃ upanandaṃ cīvarena acchādessāmī’ti."
msgstr "that they will each give you a robe.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.12"
msgid "Sopi evamāha—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.13"
msgid "‘ahampi ayyaṃ upanandaṃ cīvarena acchādessāmī’”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.14"
msgid "“Atthāvuso, maṃ te upaṭṭhākā”ti."
msgstr "“They are my supporters.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2042"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.15"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā upanando sakyaputto yena te purisā tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "Upananda then went to those men"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.16"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā te purise etadavoca—"
msgstr "and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.17"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira maṃ tumhe, āvuso, cīvarehi acchādetukāmātthā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true that you both desire to give me a robe?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.18"
msgid "“Api nayya, evaṃ hoti—"
msgstr "“Indeed,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.19"
msgid "‘ayyaṃ upanandaṃ cīvarehi acchādessāmā’”ti."
msgstr "that’s just what we were thinking.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.20"
msgid ""
"“Sace kho maṃ tumhe, āvuso, cīvarehi acchādetukāmāttha, evarūpena cīvarena "
"acchādetha,"
msgstr "“If that’s the case, then give me such-and-such a robe."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.21"
msgid "kyāhaṃ tehi acchannopi karissāmi, yānāhaṃ na paribhuñjissāmī”ti."
msgstr "For what’s the point of giving robes that I won’t use?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.22"
msgid "Atha kho te purisā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "Those men grumbled and complained,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.23"
msgid "“mahicchā ime samaṇā sakyaputtiyā asantuṭṭhā."
msgstr "“These Sakyan ascetics have great desires; they are not content."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.24"
msgid "Nayime sukarā cīvarehi acchādetuṃ."
msgstr "It’s no easy matter to give them robes."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.25"
msgid ""
"Kathañhi nāma ayyo upanando amhehi pubbe appavārito upasaṅkamitvā cīvare "
"vikappaṃ āpajjissatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"How can Venerable Upananda approach us and specify the kind of robe he wants "
"without first being invited?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.59"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2043"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.26"
msgid ""
"Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ purisānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ."
msgstr "The monks heard the complaints of those men,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.27"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "and the monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.28"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.29"
msgid ""
"“kathañhi nāma āyasmā upanando sakyaputto pubbe appavārito gahapatike "
"upasaṅkamitvā cīvare vikappaṃ āpajjissatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“How can Venerable Upananda approach lay people and make a suggestion about "
"a robe without first being invited?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2044"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.30"
msgid ""
"Atha kho te bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ upanandaṃ sakyaputtaṃ anekapariyāyena "
"vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "After criticizing him in many ways, they told the Master …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.31"
msgid ""
"“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, upananda, pubbe appavārito gahapatike upasaṅkamitvā "
"cīvare vikappaṃ āpajjasī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, Upananda, that you acted like this?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.32"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.33"
msgid "“Ñātakā te, upananda, aññātakā”ti?"
msgstr "“Are they relatives of yours?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.34"
msgid "“Aññātakā, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“No, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.35"
msgid ""
"“Aññātako, moghapurisa, aññātakānaṃ na jānāti patirūpaṃ vā appatirūpaṃ vā "
"santaṃ vā asantaṃ vā."
msgstr ""
"“Foolish man, people who are not related don’t know what’s appropriate and "
"what’s inappropriate in dealing with each other, what’s right and what’s "
"wrong."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.36"
msgid ""
"Tattha nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, pubbe appavārito aññātake gahapatike "
"upasaṅkamitvā cīvare vikappaṃ āpajjissasi."
msgstr ""
"And still you approached unrelated lay people and specified the kind of robe "
"you wanted without first being invited."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.37"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.38"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.38a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2045"></a>
#. <span class="rule"> 
#. VAR: paccekacīvaracetāpannāni upakkhaṭāni → … cetāpannā upakkhaṭā (bj) | … cetāpanā upakkhaṭā (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.39"
msgid ""
"“Bhikkhuṃ paneva uddissa ubhinnaṃ aññātakānaṃ gahapatīnaṃ vā gahapatānīnaṃ "
"vā paccekacīvaracetāpannāni upakkhaṭāni honti—"
msgstr ""
"‘If two male or female lay people have set aside separate robe funds for an "
"unrelated monk, thinking,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.40"
msgid ""
"‘imehi mayaṃ paccekacīvaracetāpannehi paccekacīvarāni cetāpetvā itthannāmaṃ "
"bhikkhuṃ cīvarehi acchādessāmā’ti;"
msgstr ""
"‘With these separate robe funds we will buy separate robes and give them to "
"monk so-and-so;’"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.41"
msgid ""
"tatra ce so bhikkhu pubbe appavārito upasaṅkamitvā cīvare vikappaṃ āpajjeyya—"
msgstr ""
"and if that monk, without first being invited, approaches them and specifies "
"the kind of robe he wants, saying,"

#. The only phrase in this rule that may be somewhat unclear is <i lang="pli">ubhova santā ekena</i>, here translated as “put together.” It seems to me that this phrase needs to be related to the main sentence verb <i lang="pli">acchādetha</i>, “present” or “give,” which takes the instrumental of the thing given: “present (him) with one (robe).” <i lang="pli">Ubhova santā</i> is explained below in the word commentary as <i lang="pli">dvepi janā</i>, “both people,” and the overall phrase then becomes, “two people present (him) with one (robe).“ This means that the funds are put together, and I translate accordingly.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.42"
msgid ""
"‘sādhu vata maṃ āyasmanto imehi paccekacīvaracetāpannehi evarūpaṃ vā "
"evarūpaṃ vā cīvaraṃ cetāpetvā acchādetha, ubhova santā ekenā’ti, "
"kalyāṇakamyataṃ upādāya, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘It would be good if you would put these separate robe funds together to buy "
"such-and-such a robe and then give it to me,’ and he does so because he "
"wants something nice, he commits and offense entailing relinquishment and "
"confession.’”"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.43"
msgid "(<em>9</em>:<strong>28</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.43a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.219"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.44"
msgid "Bhikkhuṃ paneva uddissāti"
msgstr "For a […] monk:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.45"
msgid "bhikkhussatthāya, bhikkhuṃ ārammaṇaṃ karitvā, bhikkhuṃ acchādetukāmā."
msgstr ""
"for the benefit of a monk; making a monk the object of consideration, they "
"desire to give to him."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2047"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.46"
msgid "Ubhinnanti"
msgstr "Two:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.47"
msgid "dvinnaṃ."
msgstr "a pair."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2048"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.48"
msgid "Aññātakā nāma"
msgstr "Unrelated:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.49"
msgid "mātito vā pitito vā yāva sattamā pitāmahayugā asambaddhā."
msgstr ""
"anyone who is not a descendant of one’s male ancestors going back seven "
"generations, either on the mother’s side or on the father’s side."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2049"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.50"
msgid "Gahapatī nāma"
msgstr "Male lay people:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.51"
msgid "ye keci agāraṃ ajjhāvasanti."
msgstr "any men who live in a house."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2050"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.52"
msgid "Gahapatāniyo nāma"
msgstr "Female lay people:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.53"
msgid "yā kāci agāraṃ ajjhāvasanti."
msgstr "any women who live in a house."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2051"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.54"
msgid "Cīvaracetāpannāni nāma"
msgstr "Robe funds:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.55"
msgid ""
"hiraññā vā suvaṇṇā vā muttā vā maṇī vā pavāḷā vā phalikā vā paṭakā vā suttā "
"vā kappāsā vā."
msgstr ""
"money, gold, pearls, gems, corals, crystals, cloth, thread, or cotton wool."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2052"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.56"
msgid "Imehi paccekacīvaracetāpannehīti"
msgstr "With these separate robe funds:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.57"
msgid "paccupaṭṭhitehi."
msgstr "with that which is at their disposal."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2053"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.58"
msgid "Cetāpetvāti"
msgstr "We will buy:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.59"
msgid "parivattetvā."
msgstr "having exchanged."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="14"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2054"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.60"
msgid "Acchādessāmāti"
msgstr "We will […] give:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.61"
msgid "dassāma."
msgstr "we will donate."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="15"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2055"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.62"
msgid "Tatra ce so bhikkhūti"
msgstr "If that monk:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.63"
msgid "yaṃ bhikkhuṃ uddissa cīvaracetāpannāni upakkhaṭāni honti so bhikkhu."
msgstr "the monk for whom the robe funds have been set aside."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="16"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2056"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.64"
msgid "Pubbe appavāritoti"
msgstr "Without first being invited:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.65"
msgid "pubbe avutto hoti—"
msgstr "they have not said beforehand:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.66"
msgid "“kīdisena te, bhante, cīvarena attho,"
msgstr "“Venerable, what kind of robe do you need?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.67"
msgid "kīdisaṃ te cīvaraṃ cetāpemā”ti."
msgstr "What kind of robe can we buy for you?”"

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="17"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2057"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.68"
msgid "Upasaṅkamitvāti"
msgstr "Approaches them:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.69"
msgid "gharaṃ gantvā yattha katthaci upasaṅkamitvā."
msgstr "having gone to their house or having gone wherever."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="18"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2058"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.70"
msgid "Cīvare vikappaṃ āpajjeyyāti"
msgstr "Specifies the kind of robe he wants:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.71"
msgid "āyataṃ vā hotu vitthataṃ vā appitaṃ vā saṇhaṃ vā."
msgstr "please make it long or wide or closely woven or soft."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="19"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2059"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.72"
msgid "Imehi paccekacīvaracetāpannehīti"
msgstr "These separate robe funds:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.73"
msgid "paccupaṭṭhitehi."
msgstr "that which is at their disposal."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="20"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2060"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.74"
msgid "Evarūpaṃ vā evarūpaṃ vāti"
msgstr "Such-and-such:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.75"
msgid "āyataṃ vā vitthataṃ vā appitaṃ vā saṇhaṃ vā."
msgstr "long or wide or closely woven or soft."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="21"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2061"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.76"
msgid "Cetāpetvāti"
msgstr "To buy:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.77"
msgid "parivattetvā."
msgstr "having exchanged."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="22"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2062"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.78"
msgid "Acchādethāti"
msgstr "Give:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.79"
msgid "dajjetha."
msgstr "donate."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="23"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2063"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.80"
msgid "Ubhova santā ekenāti"
msgstr "Put […] together:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.81"
msgid "dvepi janā ekena."
msgstr "two people supplying him with one robe."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="24"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2064"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.82"
msgid "Kalyāṇakamyataṃ upādāyāti"
msgstr "Because he wants something nice:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.83"
msgid "sādhatthiko mahagghatthiko."
msgstr "wanting something nice, wanting something expensive."

#. </span></p><hr><p><a class="sc" id="25"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2065"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.84"
msgid ""
"Tassa vacanena āyataṃ vā vitthataṃ vā appitaṃ vā saṇhaṃ vā cetāpenti, payoge "
"dukkaṭaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If those lay people buy a robe that is long, wide, closely woven, or soft "
"because of his statement, then for the act of making the statement, he "
"commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.61"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.85"
msgid "Paṭilābhena nissaggiyaṃ hoti."
msgstr "When he gets the robe, it becomes subject to relinquishment."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.86"
msgid "Nissajjitabbaṃ saṃghassa vā gaṇassa vā puggalassa vā."
msgstr "The robe should be relinquished to an Order, a group, or an individual."

#. <span class="kamma"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.87"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, nissajjitabbaṃ …"
msgstr "“And, monks, it should be relinquished in this way. …"

#. <span class="pe"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.88"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""
"To be expanded as in <a class=\"cr\" href=\"./pli-tv-bu-vb-np1#13\">"
"Relinquishment 1, paragraphs 13–17</a>, with appropriate substitutions. …"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.89"
msgid ""
"“idaṃ me, bhante, cīvaraṃ pubbe appavārito aññātake gahapatike upasaṅkamitvā "
"cīvare vikappaṃ āpannaṃ nissaggiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘Venerables, this robe which I received after approaching unrelated lay "
"people and specifying the kind of robe I wanted without first being invited "
"is to be relinquished."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.90"
msgid "Imāhaṃ saṃghassa nissajjāmī”ti … pe …"
msgstr "I relinquish it to the Order.’ …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.91"
msgid "dadeyyāti … pe …"
msgstr "the Order should give …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.92"
msgid "dadeyyunti … pe …"
msgstr "you should give …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.93"
msgid "āyasmato dammīti."
msgstr "‘I give this robe back to you.’”"

#. </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.93a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="26"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2066"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.94"
msgid ""
"Aññātake aññātakasaññī pubbe appavārito gahapatike upasaṅkamitvā cīvare "
"vikappaṃ āpajjati, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If the lay people are unrelated and he perceives them as unrelated, and, "
"without first being invited, he approaches them and specifies the kind of "
"robe he wants, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.95"
msgid ""
"Aññātake vematiko pubbe appavārito gahapatike upasaṅkamitvā cīvare vikappaṃ "
"āpajjati, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If the lay people are unrelated, but he is unsure if they are, and, without "
"first being invited, he approaches them and specifies the kind of robe he "
"wants, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.96"
msgid ""
"Aññātake ñātakasaññī pubbe appavārito gahapatike upasaṅkamitvā cīvare "
"vikappaṃ āpajjati, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If the lay people are unrelated, but he perceives them as related, and, "
"without first being invited, he approaches them and specifies the kind of "
"robe he wants, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="27"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2067"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.97"
msgid "Ñātake aññātakasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If the lay people are related, but he perceives them as unrelated, he commit "
"an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.98"
msgid "Ñātake vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If the lay people are related, but he is unsure if they are, he commit an "
"offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.99"
msgid "Ñātake ñātakasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr ""
"If the lay people are related and he perceives them as related, there is no "
"offense."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.99a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="28"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2068"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.100"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.101"
msgid "ñātakānaṃ,"
msgstr "if it is from relatives;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.102"
msgid "pavāritānaṃ,"
msgstr "if it is from those who have given an invitation;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.103"
msgid "aññassatthāya,"
msgstr "if it is for the benefit of another;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.104"
msgid "attano dhanena,"
msgstr "if it is by means of his own property;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.105"
msgid "mahagghaṃ cetāpetukāmānaṃ appagghaṃ cetāpeti,"
msgstr ""
"if the lay people wish to buy something expensive, but he gets them to buy "
"something inexpensive;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.106"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.107"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta"><a class="sc" id="29"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2069"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np9:pts-cs1.108"
msgid "Dutiyaupakkhaṭasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ navamaṃ."
msgstr ""
"The ninth rule, the second training rule on what is set aside, is finished."

